did.unittitle: Rockefeller University records, Assistant Business Manager, Subject Files, Series 3

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection contains 7 subseries: 1. Correspondence, 2. Civil Defense, 3. John W. Cogger – Employee Records, 4. Waldo R. Flinn – Personnel Files, 5. Insurance, 6. Miscellaneous, 7. Edric B. Smith – Subject Files

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains correspondence, subject files, minutes, budgets, personnel files and administrative information pertaining to the activities and responsibilities of the Assistant Business Manager during the year 1905-1958.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: File of correspondence dealing with the areas of responsibility of the assistant business manager.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Material from early years added to file. Much of the correspondence deals with sick leaves.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Johnson Service Co. 1915-1928. Thermostats and temperature control for animal house, greenhouse, and laboratory. Manning, Maxwell, & Moore. 1915-1916. Machine shop tools Meyer Sniffen Co. 1915-1921. Basins and faucets. Standard Scientific Co. 1914-1916. Imported glassware and Customs questions. Oscar Stolp. Animal cages. Arthur H. Thomas Co. Electric heating. Roger Williams. Automatic control for incubator heating.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: 1913-1914 Correspondence on exhibit in Lyons 1921-1925 Exhibit for Pasteur Centenary; correspondence, photographs, and programs. Includes program for exhibit at New York Academy of Medicine.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Consists primarily of correspondence with Merchants Fire Assurance Corp. dealing with coverage on both NYC and Princeton laboratories and some claims.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence with T.M. Debevoise, Better Business Bureau, and inquirers dealing with Gaylord Wilshire's useof the Institute name in medical advertising.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Primarily material regarding purchase and installation of centrafuge. Includes drawings and blueprints.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Acceptances and regrets for varied functions.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence with wish to work at RIMR under RF grant.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: 1912-1913 Womens Educational and Industrial Union 1913-1916 Primarily correspondence with Intercollegiate Bureau of Occupations, N.Y. for placement of educated women. Includes 1st report. See also Employees.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence dealing with arrangements for visitors to RIMR including announcements of some lectures.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Correspondence dealing with implication of RIMR involvement in preparation. Misleading advertising of Carrel-Dakin solution.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence and minutes; also includes brochures, enrollment cards, memos, notes, and reports.
Subjects include the cooperative civil defense program between New York Hospital and the RIMR and a manual of civil defense.

bioghist.p: John W. Cogger was appointed Personnel Supervisor in 1955 when Waldo R. Flinn was promoted to Business Manager. Cogger handled the records of non-academic personnel.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Waldo R. Flinn was Assistant Business Manager from 1927-1955, at which time he was promoted to Business Manager. He held this post until his retirement in 1965. During the time he served as Assistant Business Manager, he had the responsibility of handling the records of non-academic personnel.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence, notes, and pamphlets. Subjects include apartments leased by the Institute; background material for the Descriptive Pamphlet; New Zealand white rabbits; and tryparsamide.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Edric B. SMith was appointed to the Institute in 1913 as Assistant Business Manager. In 1918 he was appointed Acting Business Manager and then Business Manager in 1920, a post he held until his retirement in 1955. These files include the records of James U. Norris, Jerome D. Greene, and Henry James, Jr. (Smith's predecessors as Business/General Manager).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence and reports; also includes articles, building plans, contracts, notes, pamphlets, and statistics. Correspondents include Simon Flexner, Jerome D. Greene, Henry James Jr., and James U. Norris. Subjects include anti-vivisectionism, budgets, buildings, and the War Demonstration Hospital. Some personal records of Smith are also included.
